&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“Strengthening the Team &amp; Developing the Service”&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Lancashire Procurement Cluster (LPC) is the ground breaking shared service which is creating a step change in procurement and supply chain maturity for the member trusts; Blackpool Teaching Hospitals NHS FT, East Lancashire NHS Trust and Lancashire Teaching Hospitals NHS FT. It is fundamentally re-shaping the role of Procurement across the local health economy to ensure the service is fit for purpose and can deliver value and customer satisfaction in a sustainable manner. &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The LPC is hosted by ELHT but staff are based across the customer trusts and LPC estate. The vision is to deliver an excellent procurement, logistics and supplies service which focusses on continuous improvement, delivers value for the Trusts in terms of savings and efficiencies and improves outcomes for patients.&lt;/p&gt;
